story.storybody:
Jaipur, Jun 1 (PTI) Rajasthan State Industrial Development and Investment Corporation (RIICO) and State Bank of Bikaner and Jaipur (SBBJ) today signed an MoU to promote startup projects in the state.

The MoU is first of its kind aimed at boosting employment generation and creation of skilled jobs in the state. It will provide a common platform for availing assistance under the various schemes of government of India and Rajasthan government.

Speaking at the occasion, Rajasthan Chief Minister Vasundhara Raje said that the partnership will boost innovative entrepreneurship and the Single Window financial solutions would be available to new entrepreneurs to establish their business in minimal time.

Also, this will help in bringing to the fore the entrepreneurial talent from the remotest corner of the state and help them develop their business, she added. PTI SDA ADI MR
